Sometimes inheritance and instanceof are necessary when you deal with legacy or third party code. In this not so theoretical code, you have an heterogeneous hierarchy, so you can't just have something like

<code>printer.execute()</code>

More likely, you'll have something like:
<pre><code>
if (printer instanceof SillyPrinter) {
  ((SillyPrinter)printer).sillyPrint();
} else {
  printer.print();
}
</code></pre>
But that's a bit of a stretch.

